# {{name}}

A [Twill DB](https://github.com/bihaviour/twill-db) starter for **PHP** — a
serverless OLTP database embedded in-process via the `twilldb/twilldb` package
over PHP's FFI extension. No server to run, no infrastructure to provision.

## Run it

```bash
composer install
composer start
```

Requires **PHP ≥ 8.1** with the **FFI** extension enabled (`ffi.enable=1` in
`php.ini`, or the `-d ffi.enable=1` flag used by the `start` script). The native
`libengine` is located automatically; to point at one you built yourself, set
`TWILLDB_ENGINE_PATH=/abs/path/libengine.{so,dylib,dll}`.

## Frameworks

In Laravel, Symfony, or CodeIgniter, open one `Twill\Database` in a
singleton/service and reuse it across requests (the engine is a single writer per
database) — ideally on a long-lived worker (FrankenPHP, RoadRunner, Swoole).

Prefer talking Postgres instead? Run `engine-server` and point your framework's
`pgsql` connection at it (`host=127.0.0.1 port=5433 sslmode=disable`) — no FFI
needed. See the project docs for the server-mode path.

## Storage backend

The backend is chosen entirely by the connection string in `index.php`:

| Scheme | Backend |
| --- | --- |
| `file://…` | embedded, persists to a local file (this starter's default) |
| `s3://` · `r2://` · `gs://` | storage-disaggregated; credentials come from the environment |

This project is configured for `{{db_url}}`.
